'''''Skateball''''' is a [[video game]] developed by [[Ubi Soft]]. It features a violent futuristic [[sports game]] part ice skating, part soccer. It was released in [[1989 in video gaming|1989]] for the Amstrad [[Amstrad CPC|CPC]]<ref>[http://www.thelegacy.de/Museum/350/ Skateball] at thelegacy.de</ref> and [[Amstrad GX4000|GX4000]],<ref>[http://www.cpczone.net/game/1474/screens Skateball] at cpczone.net</ref> [[Atari ST]], [[Commodore 64]] and [[ZX Spectrum]].<ref>[https://spectrumcomputing.co.uk/entry/4536/ZX-Spectrum/Skateball] Skateball at spectrumcomputing.co.uk</ref>

In 1990, Ubi Soft re-issued the game with a new title: ''Skate Wars''.<ref name='ys57'>{{cite magazine |title=Skatewars|magazine=Your Sinclair |issue=33 |publisher=Future Publishing|author=Jonathan Davies|date=September 1990|page=26|url=https://spectrumcomputing.co.uk/page.php?issue_id=278&page=26|access-date=15 May 2021}}</ref> This title was also used by [[Ocean Software]] for the 1992 budget release on their ''Hit Squad'' label.<ref name='ys78'>{{cite magazine |title=The Hit Squad Advertisement|magazine=Your Sinclair |issue=78 |publisher=Future Publishing|date=June 1992|page=12|url=https://spectrumcomputing.co.uk/page.php?issue_id=299&page=12|access-date=15 May 2021}}</ref>

== Gameplay ==
A ''Skateball'' match is played by two teams on an ice court with steel walls and ball. There are several different courts with holes and other lethal obstacles. The game lacks any rules and any kind of contact is allowed.<ref>Smith, Andy; Lemmings Review in ACE 18 (Mar 1989); pp48</ref>

The game can be played by one or two players.<ref>[http://www.lemon64.com/?mainurl=http%3A//www.lemon64.com/games/details.php%3FID%3D2323 Skateball] at lemon64.com</ref> Each team has three players, one of them a goalkeeper. The object of the game is to score five goals or kill the three players of the opposite team.

